events.description: Halifax, Nova Scotia, is founded.

events.description: James Otis Jr. offends the King and Parliament in a speech to the Massachusetts General Court.

events.description: New Hampshire becomes the ninth state to ratify the Constitution of the United States.

events.description: King Louis XVI of France and his immediate family begin the Flight to Varennes during the French Revolution.

events.description: Irish Rebellion of 1798: The British Army defeats Irish rebels at the Battle of Vinegar Hill.

events.description: Peninsular War: Wellington defeats Joseph Bonaparte at the Battle of Vitoria.

events.description: Greek War of Independence: Egyptian forces capture Psara in the Aegean Sea.

events.description: Maniots defeat Egyptians under Ibrahim Pasha in the Battle of Vergas.
events.html: • 1826 – Maniots defeat Egyptians under Ibrahim Pasha in the Battle of Vergas.

events.description: In the Wallachian Revolution, Ion Heliade Rădulescu and Christian Tell issue the Proclamation of Islaz and create a new republican government.
events.html: • 1848 – In the Wallachian Revolution, Ion Heliade Rădulescu and Christian Tell issue the Proclamation of Islaz and create a new republican government.

events.description: American Civil War: The Battle of Jerusalem Plank Road begins.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: The Battle of Jerusalem Plank Road begins.

events.description: The United States captures Guam from Spain. The few warning shots fired by the U.S. naval vessels are misinterpreted as salutes by the Spanish garrison, which was unaware that the two nations were at war.

events.description: Boxer Rebellion: China formally declares war on the United States, Britain, Germany, France and Japan, as an edict issued from the Empress Dowager Cixi.
events.html: • 1900 – Boxer Rebellion: China formally declares war on the United States, Britain, Germany, France and Japan, as an edict issued from the Empress Dowager Cixi.

events.description: The Royal Canadian Mounted Police fire a volley into a crowd of unemployed war veterans, killing two, during the Winnipeg general strike.
events.html: • 1919 – The Royal Canadian Mounted Police fire a volley into a crowd of unemployed war veterans, killing two, during the Winnipeg general strike.

events.description: One-year conscription comes into force in France.

events.description: World War II: Italy begins an unsuccessful invasion of France.

events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Tobruk falls to Italian and German forces; 33,000 Allied troops are taken prisoner.[8]

events.description: Ellen Fairclough is sworn in as Canada's first female Cabinet Minister.

events.description: Cardinal Giovanni Battista Montini is elected as Pope Paul VI.
events.html: • 1963 – Cardinal Giovanni Battista Montini is elected as Pope Paul VI.

events.html: • 1982 – John Hinckley is found not guilty by reason of insanity for the attempted assassination of U.S. President Ronald Reagan.
